ZH: 身体是我们的躯体。
EN: The body is our physical vessel.

ZH: 他患有躯体疼痛。
EN: He suffers from physical pain.

ZH: 躯体健康是生活的基础。
EN: Physical health is the foundation of life.

ZH: 她通过运动锻炼来增强她的躯体素质。
EN: She enhances her physical fitness through exercise.

ZH: 躯体的病痛影响了他的工作效率。
EN: The physical ailments affected his work efficiency.

ZH: 骨骼构成了人体的躯体结构。
EN: The skeleton forms the structure of the human body.

ZH: 躯体的感觉能使我们感受到世界。
EN: The senses of the body allow us to experience the world.

ZH: 他的躯体发育均衡。
EN: His body develops in a balanced way.

ZH: 躯体活动可以促进血液循环。
EN: Physical activity can promote blood circulation.

ZH: 躯体表现出了他的情绪状态。
EN: His body displayed his emotional state.

ZH: 躯体的疼痛使他难以入睡。
EN: The physical pain made it difficult for him to fall asleep.

ZH: 躯体是心灵的驻地。
EN: The body is the dwelling place of the mind.

ZH: 她用自己的躯体保护孩子。
EN: She used her body to protect the child.

ZH: 躯体姿势可以反映一个人的心理状态。
EN: Body posture can reflect a person's psychological state.

ZH: 躯体的控制需要坚持训练。
EN: Control of the body requires consistent training.

ZH: 疾病折磨了他的躯体。
EN: The illness tormented his physical body.

ZH: 躯体的力量可以随着锻炼而增加。
EN: The strength of the body can increase with exercise.

ZH: 他在日常生活中注重保持躯体的健康。
EN: He focuses on maintaining the health of his body in daily life.

ZH: 躯体的病痛限制了她的行动能力。
EN: The physical ailments limited her ability to move.

ZH: 躯体的意义在于为我们提供行动的方式。
EN: The significance of the body lies in providing us with a means of action.
